<item>
            <title>[OAK-8711] Queries with facets should not use traversal</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-8711</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider a scenario where a query is there with facets and the traversal cost is less than the index cost that serves the facet query . This would be problematic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this case we should maybe set the traversal cost to infinity so that traversal is not an option for queries with facets.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In case there is no index available to serve this faceted query we can probably throw an exception with a meaningful message .&lt;/p&gt;</description>
